Mandilas Group Limited has donated Carrier air-conditioners to the Nigeria Centre for Disease Control (NCDC). The donation was to assist in the fight against the COVID-19 in Nigeria and to make the isolation centre in Lagos conducive for its purpose. The Mandilas team and donation were warmly received on behalf of the Director General, NCDC, by the Head Emergency Operations, Dr. Everistus Aniaku, and the Deputy Director, Central Public Health Laboratory, NCDC, Mrs. Olajumoke Babatunde. Aniaku commended Mandilas for the gesture and applauded the team for their proactiveness. Mandilas is a foremost brand in the Nigerian auto and cooling business terrain and the sole franchise distributor of Carrier Residential and Industrial ACs in Nigeria.